00:09:24,253 --> 00:09:25,814
They come and go.

82
00:09:26,174 --> 00:09:27,034
They're bought and sold.

83
00:09:27,074 --> 00:09:28,355
They're created and destroyed.

84
00:09:28,715 --> 00:09:30,276
It's always about resources.

85
00:09:30,976 --> 00:09:34,578
And by resources, I'm referring to anything that can be measured numerically.

86
00:09:35,258 --> 00:09:39,441
Which means basically, almost anything in your game could be known as a resource.

87
00:09:40,322 --> 00:09:44,104
Money, stamina, ability points, everything is an example of a resource,

88
00:09:44,525 --> 00:09:48,307
as are the items, upgrades, and even enemies that oppose the player.

89
00:09:49,448 --> 00:09:52,530
And while not all of these resources are under the player's control,

90
00:09:53,171 --> 00:09:57,033
anything the player can produce, gather, collect, and again, destroy,

91
00:09:57,874 --> 00:09:59,415
is probably a type of resource.

92
00:10:01,388 --> 00:10:04,749
