00:39:49,401 --> 00:39:53,142
to immediately go through so that by the time the new DLC was released

491
00:39:53,502 --> 00:39:55,362
they were kind of starting where they should be

492
00:39:57,874 --> 00:40:01,596
One of the things I think the Witcher did right here was to make enchantments free.

493
00:40:02,456 --> 00:40:05,197
That, considering the initial investment was quite costly,

494
00:40:05,837 --> 00:40:10,199
this is logical in the story as well as the gameplay.

495
00:40:11,020 --> 00:40:14,501
The Runewight, in a sense, owes Geralt this debt of gratitude

496
00:40:14,561 --> 00:40:19,163
for putting him back in business and restoring his ability to craft all these enchantments.

497
00:40:19,743 --> 00:40:23,265
But more importantly, I find this encourages the player to experiment

498
00:40:23,505 --> 00:40:25,926
with all of these new abilities that they've just acquired.

499
00:40:28,435 --> 00:40:31,917
Now, when we set out to design the Witcher 3 Blood and Wine expansion,

500
00:40:32,397 --> 00:40:38,141
we wanted to take you on a fantastic journey that would go far beyond the war-ravaged villages of Gnomon's Land

501
00:40:38,481 --> 00:40:41,163
and the stormy beachfronts of the Skellige Islands.

502
00:40:42,644 --> 00:40:46,367
Taken directly from the pages of the Witcher dark fantasy novels,

503
00:40:46,427 --> 00:40:53,151
the final chapter of Geralt's saga welcomes you to the Nilfgaardian realm of Tassant,

504
00:40:53,772 --> 00:40:56,353
the enchanting and mysterious land of wine.

505
00:40:57,274 --> 00:41:01,518
Heavily inspired by the beauty and the pageantry of the French-Italian countryside,

506
00:41:01,958 --> 00:41:07,443
Beauclair, the region's capital, blends rolling hills, winding roads, charming villas,

507
00:41:07,723 --> 00:41:11,326
and intriguing new characters to create a colorful and vibrant landscape

508
00:41:11,867 --> 00:41:15,770
unlike anything that we've seen in Hearts of Stone or The Wild Hunt.

509
00:41:17,369 --> 00:41:22,570
Now from an RPG perspective, this was a huge opportunity for us to add something unique as well.

510
00:41:23,330 --> 00:41:28,752
Reports we had received from our internal QA department were identifying concerns with character progression,

511
00:41:28,792 --> 00:41:34,113
where players were unable to use the ability points and inventory items that they had acquired.

512
00:41:35,033 --> 00:41:40,554
Also, feedback collected from the Witcher Online community had resulted in a list of requests

513
00:41:41,034 --> 00:41:45,695
for improvements to the user interface and new gear that would augment character abilities.

514
00:41:46,657 --> 00:41:51,044
After almost a year of the game's initial release, we felt it was time to tackle some

515
00:41:51,084 --> 00:41:56,253
of these bigger issues and, as it was the final chapter in Geralt's story, maybe have

516
00:41:56,273 --> 00:41:57,294
a little fun along the way.

517
00:41:59,368 --> 00:42:03,070
And with that in mind, along with its new region and mysterious storyline,

518
00:42:03,370 --> 00:42:07,992
we decided that Blood & Wine should introduce some all-new role-playing game mechanics as well.

519
00:42:08,993 --> 00:42:13,315
Starting with the user interface, we saw a lot of improvements,

520
00:42:13,415 --> 00:42:17,197
both with manageability and improvements to the crafting system,

521
00:42:17,237 --> 00:42:24,321
where the player is able to add a variety of components without having to leave that interface.

522
00:42:26,123 --> 00:42:35,895
We also added a new mutation system which, when used in conjunction with other ability buffs, adds an entirely new dimension to the way that you play.

523
00:42:38,165 --> 00:42:59,631
We also added a brand new design to the items where as we were placing things through the world it became clear again with quest designers needing support, with arts needing support, with gameplay needing support, we needed a chance and a rule set maybe to keep all this content placing consistently.

524
00:43:01,885 --> 00:43:07,253
Finally, we started looking at an all-new dye system where we were giving players the

525
00:43:07,313 --> 00:43:10,178
ability to customize the color of the Witcher's armor sets.

526
00:43:13,054 --> 00:43:17,196
Perhaps the biggest change of these was the mutation system.

527
00:43:18,317 --> 00:43:20,298
It introduces a new RPG design,

528
00:43:21,098 --> 00:43:26,020
and while this mechanic was originally added to compensate for the expansion's high-level requirements,

529
00:43:26,740 --> 00:43:30,482
we ultimately found that it was able to address a lot of other concerns as well.

530
00:43:31,723 --> 00:43:34,344
Primarily, the first is related to character progression.

531
00:43:35,750 --> 00:43:38,773
See, as players run around the Witcher's vast open world,

532
00:43:39,174 --> 00:43:41,857
they encounter a variety of different monsters and enemies,

533
00:43:42,237 --> 00:43:44,059
some of which are extremely powerful

534
00:43:44,439 --> 00:43:48,143
and require players to achieve a high level

535
00:43:48,243 --> 00:43:49,284
in order to defeat them.

536
00:43:50,145 --> 00:43:51,947
Encountering these types of situations

537
00:43:52,447 --> 00:43:54,049
encourages the players to progress

538
00:43:54,409 --> 00:43:56,271
in order to overcome the challenges

539
00:43:56,691 --> 00:43:58,353
and acquire the rewards that await.

540
00:44:00,175 --> 00:44:04,799
This is one of the things that I feel sets the Witcher apart from some of the other RPGs on the market.

541
00:44:05,880 --> 00:44:09,584
See, instead of increasing the strength of each monster and enemy,

542
00:44:10,285 --> 00:44:17,151
based on the level of the player, the difficulty is fixed and at times can overwhelm even the most talented Witcher.

543
00:44:18,252 --> 00:44:24,839
The key takeaway here is that to ensure the player actually feels like they're getting

544
00:44:24,919 --> 00:44:28,482
stronger there's some things that we want to be careful to deliver.

545
00:44:29,643 --> 00:44:35,609
The problem with continually scaling enemies is that by basing them on the player's level

546
00:44:35,649 --> 00:44:39,233
the player may never actually feel that they're progressing.

547
00:44:40,034 --> 00:44:45,986
that as that same challenge progresses, they're progressing and you get this kind of arms race

548
00:44:46,047 --> 00:44:51,198
where you end up with a very flat and normalized experience as the game runs through.

549
00:44:53,180 --> 00:45:05,111
In The Witcher, character progression is limited by a combination of experience and ability points that limit the games that they complete, story quests, side quests, and witcher contracts.

550
00:45:05,972 --> 00:45:15,360
In the beginning, this limitation forces the player to plan and carefully select its abilities in order to build strengths that focus on their particular playstyle.

551
00:45:16,595 --> 00:45:21,198
Unfortunately, based on the feedback that we had received, as players were increasing

552
00:45:21,238 --> 00:45:24,240
a level, this progression curve was actually peaking too early.

553
00:45:24,260 --> 00:45:29,163
This was leading to a disappointment in the endgame, where players were feeling little

554
00:45:29,404 --> 00:45:30,845
to no progression at all.

555
00:45:33,120 --> 00:45:36,661
The issue was actually a flaw in the way that the skill tree was designed.

556
00:45:37,302 --> 00:45:41,983
In this example, you can see here that once all the skill points have been allocated,

557
00:45:42,103 --> 00:45:47,125
once all the skill slots have been filled, and their abilities maxed out, the player

558
00:45:47,165 --> 00:45:49,685
has no motivation to continue leveling up.

559
00:45:50,786 --> 00:45:55,867
And this resulting effect is that as players progress, they will continue to accumulate

560
00:45:55,927 --> 00:45:59,428
ability points that cannot be allocated within the skill tree.

561
00:46:00,541 --> 00:46:04,663
Also, if you look along both sides of the skill tree, you'll see that four monster mutagens

562
00:46:06,004 --> 00:46:07,925
all are suffering from the same problem.

563
00:46:09,026 --> 00:46:12,388
These slots have been filled and with no way to continue utilizing them.

564
00:46:13,008 --> 00:46:17,911
As Geralt continues to defeat boss-type monsters and collect these powerful items,

565
00:46:18,651 --> 00:46:21,973
they will just simply continue to stack up inside the player's inventory.

566
00:46:23,074 --> 00:46:26,576
And to resolve these issues, we came up with the mutation system.

567
00:46:27,723 --> 00:46:33,767
See, mutations are powerful abilities that can be added to Geralt's skill set in addition

568
00:46:33,827 --> 00:46:35,408
to his regular character skills.

569
00:46:36,589 --> 00:46:43,053
With 12 mutations in total, and each one embodying a very specific skill type, whether it be

570
00:46:43,133 --> 00:46:48,176
combat, alchemy, science, or a blend of these types, the players are able to choose how

571
00:46:48,216 --> 00:46:49,276
they progress once again.

572
00:46:51,055 --> 00:46:56,139
In order to activate a mutation, it actually has to be first researched, which also costs

573
00:46:56,179 --> 00:47:00,982
an increasing amount of both skill points and greater mutagens.

574
00:47:02,003 --> 00:47:06,906
Additionally, these mutations build on each other, which focuses players to unlock the

575
00:47:06,966 --> 00:47:11,770
lower mutations before advancing to the more advanced options that are made available.

576
00:47:12,625 --> 00:47:17,286
and although they are labeled as game-changing abilities with effects like free respawn on

577
00:47:17,346 --> 00:47:21,447
death several could be considered more of a game breaker.

578
00:47:22,427 --> 00:47:27,849
And in fact one of my personal favorites is a freezing effect that it adds to the art

579
00:47:27,889 --> 00:47:32,810
sign ability where either they're frozen or they completely explode and like frozen jibs

580
00:47:32,870 --> 00:47:34,190
and fly all over the place.

581
00:47:34,490 --> 00:47:35,451
It's a real blast.

582
00:47:38,933 --> 00:47:44,499
Finally, when the mutation is equipped, the Strengthened Synapses ability also expands

583
00:47:44,599 --> 00:47:51,485
Gero's skill tree with one additional ability slot for every two mutations that he researches.

584
00:47:52,416 --> 00:47:57,480
Putting all of these things together, the mutation system turned into a massive step

585
00:47:57,520 --> 00:48:03,025
forward in regards to resolving our issues with character progression, as well as fixing

586
00:48:03,325 --> 00:48:06,247
and making more fun inside the player's skill tree.

587
00:48:07,228 --> 00:48:12,633
We were able to eliminate concerns with unused inventory by providing the player new opportunities

588
00:48:12,793 --> 00:48:14,835
to spend the ability points they had collected.

589
00:48:15,768 --> 00:48:20,652
And by focusing on monster mutagens, we were able to expand the need once again for the

590
00:48:20,772 --> 00:48:26,016
alchemy system and further encourage the player to invest time in the monster hunt mechanic.

591
00:48:27,513 --> 00:48:31,758
In addition to resolving these issues, this decision provides the player with new motivation

592
00:48:32,298 --> 00:48:37,704
to continue leveling up, but also, importantly, it further immerses the player within the

593
00:48:37,824 --> 00:48:44,251
Witcher's Monster Slayer fantasy, making it a perfect addition to the existing roleplaying

594
00:48:44,311 --> 00:48:45,653
experience that we had created.

595
00:48:48,674 --> 00:48:53,419
Now considering this vast change in dynamics that Blood & Wine brings to The Witcher 3,

596
00:48:54,060 --> 00:48:58,064
we felt it would be a lot of fun to bring some of that color into the crafting system.

