00:49:17,379 --> 00:49:21,685
Considering many RPGs let you design the protagonist of the story from the outset,

601
00:49:22,526 --> 00:49:26,351
a lot of players were feeling discouraged that they weren't given more options throughout the game.

602
00:49:28,225 --> 00:49:34,127
While everybody was on board with the idea, there was a technical issue involved with how player armors were designed.

603
00:49:35,187 --> 00:49:42,389
Instead of using two channels to separate the colors, the same process that we use to randomize NPC appearances,

604
00:49:43,189 --> 00:49:52,212
character artists had made a very early decision to focus on delivering high quality assets that would only use a single channel process.

605
00:49:54,014 --> 00:49:58,657
This required me to modify several code paths that had not been touched in years,

606
00:49:58,817 --> 00:50:05,440
which presents a lot of concerns as we no longer had an in-house expert to consult if things go wrong.

607
00:50:06,421 --> 00:50:11,543
Additionally, new textures and materials would have to be created, not only per armor,

608
00:50:11,884 --> 00:50:15,986
but per armor piece before these new code changes could take effect.

609
00:50:18,495 --> 00:50:24,199
But putting together a prototype, I was able to finally modify the Griffon armor and demonstrate

610
00:50:24,219 --> 00:50:29,063
the quality and number of new assets that we could generate from the game base mesh.

611
00:50:31,156 --> 00:50:36,819
The best part, I feel, is that once released, not only is this a huge step forward in providing

612
00:50:36,839 --> 00:50:41,321
the player with a completely new level of customization that they had not yet known

