00:51:23,086 --> 00:51:30,851
We also include like a die remover, which if you did make a mistake or prefer to undie something or mix and match however you want,

624
00:51:31,191 --> 00:51:34,374
that's also a mechanic that you can incorporate into your play.

625
00:51:35,455 --> 00:51:40,839
Also, this came with a new preview mode where you could present these colors on each mesh

626
00:51:41,420 --> 00:51:44,082
individually before you actually apply them.

627
00:51:44,683 --> 00:51:49,847
And this was nice so that if you had the idea of mixing colors as I was just showing you,

628
00:51:50,007 --> 00:51:54,852
two or three different colors in a single armor set, this would allow you to see how

629
00:51:54,972 --> 00:51:57,514
each color plays out on each different piece of armor.

630
00:51:59,412 --> 00:52:05,057
You know, thinking back over all of these new features, for me, I'd say this one was my favorite.

631
00:52:06,118 --> 00:52:09,240
Unlike an ancestral sword that kind of deals more damage,

632
00:52:09,961 --> 00:52:13,583
or a piece of relic armor that provides a greater resistance to injury,

